item.title: [ENTESB-134] REST and secure-rest examples fail to install on XP
item.description:
I get the following errors when trying to install the rest and secure-rest examples on XP. I checked with Gert, who said it was not a problem with the examples but "At best, that looks like a problem with etc/jre.properties or something like that in the Windows assembly... It might also be a problem with new OSGi locator stuff, so that's why the configuration error is "at best" "

item.summary: REST and secure-rest examples fail to install on XP

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Fixed by removing the org.apache.servicemix.specs.timeout property from the karaf.bat file (it was already removed from the unix karaf shell script a while ago) cfr. http://fusesource.com/forge/git/karaf.git/?p=karaf.git;a=commit;h=a677ae6e38e21bfeace7cb6981b0f1b066208c4a
The issue would also never have surfaced if we wouldn't have had the mismatch in specs versions - raised ENTESB-146 to ensure those get aligned again.
